{"serial": "48002", "department_serial": 42, "code": "FM2009", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Introduction to Civil Law", "ch": "民法概要"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Lu, Chi-Yuan"], "ch": ["魯志遠"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 5, "session": ["6", "7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "I1", "room": "004"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 70, "department": {"ch": "財務金融學系", "en": "Department of Finance"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 1, "selected": 70, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "課程建立對民法的基本理解，並且具備解決一些基本法律問題的能力，透過系統性的學習，讓學生將能瞭解民法在生活、商業和社會關係中作用，並且能夠運用這些知識來解決實際法律問題。主要目標有三:\n一、理解民法體系重點,包括財產行為(如買賣、租賃等)與身分行為(如親屬繼承)。二、掌握基本概念並幫助學生理解法律在社會中的重要性，並促進他們的法律意識,如網站標錯價案,消費者和廠商各自主張如何。\n三、培養團隊合作與溝通能力： 透過小組報告活動，培養團隊合作和溝通能力，並學會在合作中共同解決法律問題，融會貫通民法五編問題。", "en": "The course aims to establish a fundamental understanding of civil law and equip students with the ability to address basic legal issues. Through systematic learning, students will gain insight into the role of civil law in daily life, business, and social relationships. They will be able to apply this knowledge to solve practical legal problems. The main objectives are threefold:\n一、To comprehend key aspects of the civil law system, encompassing property transactions (such as buying, selling, leasing, etc.) and personal status matters (like familial inheritance).\n二、To grasp essential concepts and facilitate students‘ understanding of the significance of law in society, fostering their legal awareness. For instance, in cases of pricing errors on websites, students will explore how consumers and businesses present their respective claims.\n三、To cultivate teamwork and communication skills: Through group presentation activities, students will develop their collaborative and communication abilities, learning to collaboratively address legal issues and integrate the principles from the five divisions of civil law."}, "outline": {"ch": "民法係法律的第一堂課，規範私人生活的法律，分為總則編、債編、物權編、親屬編及繼承編，我國民法五篇理論體系完備，邏輯結構嚴謹，是內容豐富、實用性最高的法律學科。民法概要關注合同當事人的自由意願、平等和誠實信用等原則，深入理解民法的核心原則和應用。培養縝密的邏輯思考能力。\n教學目標首重於使同學認識民法有關之原理原則、法律概念，並就授課科目作綜合說明及概要敘述，及介紹重要法院裁判、具體事例等實務見解，期能讓同學們於學習民法理論時亦能與實務結合。\n實際上的課程可能根據教學目標、學生需求和課程長度進行調整和擴充。", "en": "The first class of the Civil Law Department is the law that regulates private life. It is divided into the General Principles, Debts, Property Rights, Relatives, and Inheritance. The five chapters of Chinese Civil Law have a complete theoretical system and a rigorous logical structure, making them the most informative and practical legal discipline. The summary of civil law focuses on the principles of free will, equality, and good faith of contract parties, and deeply understands the core principles and applications of civil law. Cultivate meticulous logical thinking skills.\nThe teaching objective is primarily to enable students to understand the principles and legal concepts related to civil law, and to provide a comprehensive explanation and summary of the teaching subjects, as well as introduce important court judgments, specific examples, and other practical insights, in order to enable students to integrate civil law theory with practice.\nThe actual curriculum may be adjusted and expanded based on teaching objectives, student needs, and course length."}, "textbook": {"ch": "依上課規定", "en": "According to the rules of the class"}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "100", "en": "100"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "平常表現(出席率)：10％\n小組報告(含書面資料)：30％\n期末考：60％“", "en": "Class Participation (attendance rate) 10％\nQuiz group report (including written materials): 30％\nFinal Test 60％"}, "officeHour": {"ch": "請洽老師", "en": "by appointment"}, "teachWeeks": {"ch": "16+2", "en": "16+2"}, "flexDiscription": {"ch": "自主學習及補救教學等", "en": "Self-learning and remedial teaching, 